Open redirect in PieRegister Wordpress plugin 
---------------------------------------------

*About*: PieRegister as described on their site:

> A WordPress Registration Plugin. Use it to create Registration Pages and Forms for your WordPress site.

*Description*: The logout functionality of PieRegister 2.0.21 contains an open redirect allowing an attacker to redirect to a malicious page to conduct phishing or malware install attempts

*Vendor*: [GeneTech Solutions](http://www.genetechsolutions.com)

*Timeline*

* 2016-07-05: Vendor Notified

*Vulnerability*: pie-register.php doesn't require authentication to use the redirect option when logging out:

    /////////////// PIEREG LOGOUT ////////////////
    if( (isset($_GET['piereg_logout_url']) and isset($_GET['redirect_to'])) and ($_GET['piereg_logout_url'] == "true") ){
        $redirect_to = (!empty($_GET['redirect_to']))? urldecode($_GET['redirect_to']) : home_url();
        wp_logout();
        wp_redirect($redirect_to);
        exit;
    }


*Proof of Concept*: Simply modifying the redirect_to GET parameter
  
> http://wordpresshost/?piereg_logout_url=true&redirect_to=https://example.com

*Further Reading*: More information on open redirects [here](https://www.owasp.org/index.php/Top_10_2013-A10-Unvalidated_Redirects_and_Forwards)
